#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn14:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 14 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 14 "

# NOTE: The title is not easy to translate. There is no reason to think apadāna was yet in use as a standard term for “story of past lives”; rather, such usage derived from here. Chinese versions of the text have completely different titles: “Seven Buddhas”, “The Great Root”, “Vipassi Buddha”, “The Lineage of the Seven Past Buddhas”. Only the second of these might relate to the Pali. The sense seems to have been “(story about) reaping results of deeds”.
#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn14:0.2"
msgid "Mahāpadānasutta "
msgstr "The Great Discourse on the Harvest of Deeds "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:0.3"
msgid "1. Pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttakathā "
msgstr "1. On Past Lives "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1.1, pts-vp-pli2.1, sc1
msgctxt "dn14:1.1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
# NOTE: Kareri doesn’t seem to have a recognized English name.
msgctxt "dn14:1.1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme karerikuṭikāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery, in the hut by the <i>kareri</i> tree. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ karerimaṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttā dhammī kathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Then after the meal, on return from alms-round, several senior mendicants sat together in the pavilion by the <i>kareri</i> tree and this Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives came up among them, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.1.4"
msgid "“itipi pubbenivāso, itipi pubbenivāso”ti. "
msgstr "“So it was in a past life; such it was in a past life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.2, sc2
msgctxt "dn14:1.2.1"
msgid "Assosi kho bhagavā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ. "
msgstr "With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha heard that discussion among the mendicants. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena karerimaṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi, nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "So he got up from his seat and went to the pavilion, where he sat on the seat spread out and addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.3"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.4"
msgid "kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "What conversation was unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.2, sc3
msgctxt "dn14:1.2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.6"
msgid "“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ karerimaṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttā dhammī kathā udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.7"
msgid "‘itipi pubbenivāso itipi pubbenivāso’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.2.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā. Atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti. "
msgstr "“This is the conversation that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.3, sc4
msgctxt "dn14:1.3.1"
msgid "“Iccheyyātha no tumhe, bhikkhave, pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ sotun”ti? "
msgstr "“Would you like to hear a Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.3.2"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo; "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

#. VAR: bhagavato sutvā → bhagavato vacanaṃ sutvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:1.3.3"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavā pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyya, bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti. "
msgstr "Let the Buddha give a Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives. The mendicants will listen and remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.3.4"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha sādhukaṃ manasi karotha bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.3.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.4, sc5
#. VAR: ekanavutikappe → ekanavuto kappo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.4.1"
msgid "“Ito so, bhikkhave, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "“Ninety-one eons ago, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

#. VAR: ekatiṃse kappe → ekatiṃso kappo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.4.2"
msgid "Ito so, bhikkhave, ekatiṃse kappe yaṃ sikhī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "Thirty-one eons ago, the Buddha Sikhī arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.4.3"
msgid "Tasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, ekatiṃse kappe vessabhū bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "In the same thirty-first eon, the Buddha Vessabhū arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

#. VAR: Imasmiññeva → imasmiṃ yeva (km, pts1) | imasmiṃ (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn14:1.4.4"
msgid "Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "In the present fortunate eon, the Buddhas Kakusandha, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.4.5"
msgid "Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe koṇāgamano bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.4.6"
msgid "Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "and Kassapa arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.4.7"
msgid "Imasmiññeva kho, bhikkhave, bhaddakappe ahaṃ etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno. "
msgstr "And in the present fortunate eon, I have arisen in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.5, pts-vp-pli2.3, sc6
msgctxt "dn14:1.5.1"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr "The Buddhas Vipassī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.2"
msgid "Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr "Sikhī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.3"
msgid "Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr "and Vessabhū were born as aristocrats into aristocrat families. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.4"
msgid "Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, brāhmaṇakule udapādi. "
msgstr "The Buddhas Kakusandha, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, brāhmaṇakule udapādi. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.6"
msgid "Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brāhmaṇo jātiyā ahosi, brāhmaṇakule udapādi. "
msgstr "and Kassapa were born as brahmins into brahmin families. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.5.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosiṃ, khattiyakule uppanno. "
msgstr "I was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.6, sc7
msgctxt "dn14:1.6.1"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "Koṇḍañña was the clan of Vipassī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.2"
msgid "Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "Sikhī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.3"
msgid "Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "and Vessabhū. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.4"
msgid "Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "Kassapa was the clan of Kakusandha, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.6"
msgid "Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kassapo gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "and Kassapa. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.6.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho gotamo gottena ahosiṃ. "
msgstr "Gotama is my clan. "

# NOTE: Both RD and MW say this is the lifespan in that eon. And it is true that this is the normal usage of ayuppamana. However, in such cases the subject in genitive is given as plural, to denote the entire generation, etc. Here it is singular, and specifies only Vipassi. Sure, it’s likely that this would have been typical, but I don’t think that’s what the text is saying. Note that when the Buddha speaks of his own life, he uses a different phrasing. If ayuppamana here referred to the lifespan of the current generation, there would be no reason for the Buddha to not apply it to himself. But if it means that of the individual, then it makes sense why he would shift to a more indirect statement.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.7, pts-vp-pli2.4, sc8
msgctxt "dn14:1.7.1"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Vipassī lived for 80,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.2"
msgid "Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sattativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Sikhī lived for 70,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.3"
msgid "Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa saṭṭhivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Vessabhū lived for 60,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.4"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa cattālīsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Kakusandha lived for 40,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tiṃsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana lived for 30,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.6"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa vīsativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "Kassapa lived for 20,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.7.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ; yo ciraṃ jīvati, so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo. "
msgstr "For me these days the life-span is short, brief, and fleeting. A long-lived person lives for a century or a little more. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.8, sc9
msgctxt "dn14:1.8.1"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Vipassī was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree. "

# NOTE: puṇḍarīka is the white lotus; Comm says this is setamba, which must have been a tree with lotus-like flowers, I guess.
msgctxt "dn14:1.8.2"
msgid "Sikhī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho puṇḍarīkassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Sikhī was awakened at the root of a white-mango tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.8.3"
msgid "Vessabhū, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sālassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Vessabhū was awakened at the root of a <i>sal</i> tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.8.4"
msgid "Kakusandho, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sirīsassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Kakusandha was awakened at the root of an acacia tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.8.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamano, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho udumbarassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana was awakened at the root of a cluster fig tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.8.6"
msgid "Kassapo, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nigrodhassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "Kassapa was awakened at the root of a banyan tree. "

# NOTE: peepul seems to be the most common of the many words for the Bodhi tree.
msgctxt "dn14:1.8.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho assatthassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "I was awakened at the root of a peepul tree. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.9, pts-vp-pli2.5, sc10
msgctxt "dn14:1.9.1"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Vipassī had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.2"
msgid "Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa abhibhūsambhavaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Sikhī had a fine pair of chief disciples named Abhibhū and Sambhava. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.3"
msgid "Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa soṇuttaraṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Vessabhū had a fine pair of chief disciples named Soṇa and Uttara. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.4"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa vidhurasañjīvaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Kakusandha had a fine pair of chief disciples named Vidhura and Sañjīva. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhiyyosuttaraṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had a fine pair of chief disciples named Bhiyyosa and Uttara. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.6"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tissabhāradvājaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Kassapa had a fine pair of chief disciples named Tissa and Bhāradvāja. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.9.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "I have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna. "

# NOTE: Both RD and MW have “assemblies”, which is a little misleading. It doesn’t refer to permanent groupings, but events.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.10, sc11
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.1"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni. Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Vipassī had three gatherings of disciples—one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.2"
msgid "Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sattatibhikkhusahassāni. Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Sikhī had three gatherings of disciples—one of 100,000, one of 80,000, and one of 70,000—all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.3"
msgid "Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sattatibhikkhusahassāni, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi saṭṭhibhikkhusahassāni. Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Vessabhū had three gatherings of disciples—one of 80,000, one of 70,000, and one of 60,000—all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.4"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi cattālīsabhikkhusahassāni. Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Kakusandha had one gathering of disciples—40,000 mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.6, sc15
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi tiṃsabhikkhusahassāni. Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had one gathering of disciples—30,000 mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.6"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi vīsatibhikkhusahassāni. Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "Kassapa had one gathering of disciples—20,000 mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "dn14:1.10.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni. Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "I have had one gathering of disciples—1,250 mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.11, sc18
msgctxt "dn14:1.11.1"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Vipassī had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.2"
msgid "Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khemaṅkaro nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Sikhī had as chief attendant a mendicant named Khemaṅkara. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.3"
msgid "Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa upasanto nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Vessabhū had as chief attendant a mendicant named Upasanta. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.4"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa buddhijo nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Kakusandha had as chief attendant a mendicant named Buddhija. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.5"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sotthijo nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had as chief attendant a mendicant named Sotthija. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.6"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sabbamitto nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "Kassapa had as chief attendant a mendicant named Sabbamitta. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.11.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi ānando nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "I have as chief attendant a mendicant named Ānanda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.12, pts-vp-pli2.7, sc19
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.1"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Vipassī’s father was King Bandhuma, "

#. VAR: janetti → janettī (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.2"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.3"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.4"
msgid "Sikhissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa aruṇo nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Sikhī’s father was King Aruṇa, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.5"
msgid "Pabhāvatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Pabhāvatī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.6"
msgid "Aruṇassa rañño aruṇavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and their capital city was named Aruṇavatī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
#. VAR: suppatito nāma → suppatīto nāma (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.7"
msgid "Vessabhussa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa suppatito nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Vessabhū’s father was King Suppatīta, "

#. VAR: Vassavatī nāma → yasavatī nāma (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.8"
msgid "Vassavatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Vassavatī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.9"
msgid "Suppatitassa rañño anomaṃ nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and their capital city was named Suppatīta. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.10"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa aggidatto nāma brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Kakusandha’s father was the brahmin Aggidatta, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.11"
msgid "Visākhā nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Visākhā. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.12"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena khemo nāma rājā ahosi. "
msgstr "At that time the king was Khema, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.13"
msgid "Khemassa rañño khemavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "whose capital city was named Khemavatī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.14"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa yaññadatto nāma brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana’s father was the brahmin Yaññadatta, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.15"
msgid "Uttarā nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Uttarā. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.16"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena sobho nāma rājā ahosi. "
msgstr "At that time the king was Sobha, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.17"
msgid "Sobhassa rañño sobhavatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "whose capital city was named Sobhavatī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
#. VAR: nāma → kiṃkī nāma (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.18"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa brahmadatto nāma brāhmaṇo pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Kassapa’s father was the brahmin Brahmadatta, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.19"
msgid "Dhanavatī nāma brāhmaṇī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "and his birth mother was the brahmin lady Dhanavatī. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.20"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kikī nāma rājā ahosi. "
msgstr "At that time the king was Kikī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.21"
msgid "Kikissa rañño bārāṇasī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "whose capital city was named Benares. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.22"
msgid "Mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi suddhodano nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "My father was King Suddhodana, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.23"
msgid "Māyā nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "my birth mother was Queen Māyā, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.24"
msgid "Kapilavatthu nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosī”ti. "
msgstr "and our capital city was Kapilavatthu.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.12.25"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.12.26"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi. "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.13, pts-vp-pli2.8, sc26
msgctxt "dn14:1.13.1"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants discussed among themselves: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.13.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, reverends, it’s amazing, the power and might of a Realized One! "

msgctxt "dn14:1.13.3"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarissati, nāmatopi anussarissati, gottatopi anussarissati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarissati, sāvakayugatopi anussarissati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarissati: "
msgstr "For he is able to recollect the caste, names, clans, life-span, chief disciples, and gatherings of disciples of the Buddhas of the past who have become completely extinguished, cut off proliferation, cut off the track, finished off the cycle, and transcended suffering. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.13.4"
msgid "‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti. "
msgstr "He knows the caste they were born in, and also their names, clans, conduct, qualities, wisdom, meditation, and freedom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.9, sc27
msgctxt "dn14:1.13.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, tathāgatasseva nu kho esā dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: ‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti, "
msgstr "Is it because the Realized One has clearly comprehended the principle of the teachings that he can recollect all these things? "

msgctxt "dn14:1.13.6"
msgid "udāhu devatā tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: ‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti. "
msgstr "Or did deities tell him?” "

msgctxt "dn14:1.13.7"
msgid "Ayañca hidaṃ tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antarākathā vippakatā hoti. "
msgstr "But this conversation among those mendicants was left unfinished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.14, sc28
msgctxt "dn14:1.14.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena karerimaṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the pavilion by the <i>kareri</i> tree, where he sat on the seat spread out "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.2"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.3"
msgid "“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.4"
msgid "kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "What conversation was unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.10, sc29
msgctxt "dn14:1.14.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.6"
msgid "“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato ayaṃ antarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.7"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.8"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarissati, nāmatopi anussarissati, gottatopi anussarissati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarissati, sāvakayugatopi anussarissati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarissati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.9"
msgid "“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.10"
msgid "Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, tathāgatasseva nu kho esā dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.11"
msgid "“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.12"
msgid "Udāhu devatā tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.13"
msgid "“evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī”’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.14.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti. "
msgstr "“This was our conversation that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.15, sc30
msgctxt "dn14:1.15.1"
msgid "“Tathāgatassevesā, bhikkhave, dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: "
msgstr "“It is because the Realized One has clearly comprehended the principle of the teachings that he can recollect all these things. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.15.2"
msgid "‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.15.3"
msgid "Devatāpi tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati: "
msgstr "And the deities also told me. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.15.4"
msgid "‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.11, sc31
msgctxt "dn14:1.15.5"
msgid "Iccheyyātha no tumhe, bhikkhave, bhiyyoso mattāya pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ sotun”ti? "
msgstr "Would you like to hear a further Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.15.6"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo; "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "dn14:1.15.7"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavā bhiyyoso mattāya pubbenivāsapaṭisaṃyuttaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyya, bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti. "
msgstr "Let the Buddha give a further Dhamma talk on the subject of past lives. The mendicants will listen and remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.15.8"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.15.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.15.10"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.16, pts-vp-pli2.12, sc32
msgctxt "dn14:1.16.1"
msgid "“Ito so, bhikkhave, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "“Ninety-one eons ago, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.2"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr "He was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.3"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "His clan was Koṇḍañña. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.4"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "He lived for 80,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.5"
msgid "Vipassī, bhikkhave, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "He was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.6"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "He had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.7"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "He had three gatherings of disciples—"

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.8"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni. "
msgstr "one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—"

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.9"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.10"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "He had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.11"
msgid "Vipassissa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "His father was King Bandhuma, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.12"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.16.13"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:1.16.14"
msgid "2. Bodhisattadhammatā "
msgstr "2. What’s Normal For One Intent on Awakening "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.17, sc33
msgctxt "dn14:1.17.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto tusitā kāyā cavitvā sato sampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkami. "
msgstr "When Vipassī, the being intent on awakening, passed away from the host of Joyful Gods, he was conceived in his mother’s womb, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (1) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn14:1.17.3"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto tusitā kāyā cavitvā mātukucchiṃ okkamati. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening passes away from the host of Joyful Gods, he is conceived in his mother’s womb. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.4"
msgid "Atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "And then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.5"
msgid "Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā, yatthapime candimasūriyā evaṃmahiddhikā evaṃmahānubhāvā ābhāya nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.6"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā, tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti: ‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr "And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light: ‘So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.7"
msgid "Ayañca dasasahassī lokadhātu saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati. Appamāṇo ca uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "And this galaxy shakes and rocks and trembles. And an immeasurable, magnificent light appears in the world, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.8"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (2) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
#. VAR: catuddisaṃ → cātuddisaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.17.9"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, cattāro naṃ devaputtā catuddisaṃ rakkhāya upagacchanti: ‘mā naṃ bodhisattaṃ vā bodhisattamātaraṃ vā manusso vā amanusso vā koci vā viheṭhesī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, four gods approach to guard the four directions, so that no human or non-human or anyone at all shall harm the being intent on awakening or his mother. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.17.10"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (3) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.18, pts-vp-pli2.13, sc36
msgctxt "dn14:1.18.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, pakatiyā sīlavatī bodhisattamātā hoti, viratā pāṇātipātā, viratā adinnādānā, viratā kāmesumicchācārā, viratā musāvādā, viratā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, she becomes naturally ethical. She refrains from killing living creatures, stealing, sexual misconduct, lying, and alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.18.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (4) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.19, sc37
msgctxt "dn14:1.19.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na bodhisattamātu purisesu mānasaṃ uppajjati kāmaguṇūpasaṃhitaṃ, anatikkamanīyā ca bodhisattamātā hoti kenaci purisena rattacittena. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, she no longer feels sexual desire for men, and she cannot be violated by a man of lustful intent. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.19.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (5) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.20, sc38
msgctxt "dn14:1.20.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, lābhinī bodhisattamātā hoti pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ. Sā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricāreti. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, she obtains the five kinds of sensual stimulation and amuses herself, supplied and provided with them. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.20.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (6) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.21, pts-vp-pli2.14, sc39
msgctxt "dn14:1.21.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na bodhisattamātu kocideva ābādho uppajjati. Sukhinī bodhisattamātā hoti akilantakāyā, bodhisattañca bodhisattamātā tirokucchigataṃ passati sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, no afflictions beset her. She’s happy and free of bodily fatigue. And she sees the being intent on awakening in her womb, complete with all his various parts, not deficient in any faculty. "

#. VAR: Tatrāssa → tatra yaṃ (bj) | tatrassa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.21.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno. Tatrāssa suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all good qualities. And it was strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.21.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso hatthe karitvā paccavekkheyya: ‘ayaṃ kho maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno. Tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā’ti. "
msgstr "And someone with good eyesight were to take it in their hand and examine it: ‘This beryl gem is naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all good qualities. And it’s strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.21.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchiṃ okkanto hoti, na bodhisattamātu kocideva ābādho uppajjati, sukhinī bodhisattamātā hoti akilantakāyā, bodhisattañca bodhisattamātā tirokucchigataṃ passati sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, when the being intent on awakening is conceived in his mother’s belly, no afflictions beset her. She’s happy and free of bodily fatigue. And she sees the being intent on awakening in her womb, complete with all his various parts, not deficient in any faculty. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.21.5"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (7) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.22, sc40
msgctxt "dn14:1.22.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, sattāhajāte bodhisatte bodhisattamātā kālaṃ karoti tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, seven days after the being intent on awakening is born, his mother passes away and is reborn in the host of Joyful Gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.22.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (8) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.23, sc41
msgctxt "dn14:1.23.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yathā aññā itthikā nava vā dasa vā māse gabbhaṃ kucchinā pariharitvā vijāyanti, na hevaṃ bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati. Daseva māsāni bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā kucchinā pariharitvā vijāyati. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, while other women carry the infant in the womb for nine or ten months before giving birth, not so the mother of the being intent on awakening. She gives birth after exactly ten months. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.23.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (9) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.24, sc42
msgctxt "dn14:1.24.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yathā aññā itthikā nisinnā vā nipannā vā vijāyanti, na hevaṃ bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati. Ṭhitāva bodhisattaṃ bodhisattamātā vijāyati. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, while other women give birth while sitting or lying down, not so the mother of the being intent on awakening. She only gives birth standing up. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.24.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (10) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.25, sc43
msgctxt "dn14:1.25.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, devā paṭhamaṃ paṭiggaṇhanti, pacchā manussā. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, gods receive him first, then humans. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.25.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (11) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.26, sc44
msgctxt "dn14:1.26.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, appattova bodhisatto pathaviṃ hoti, cattāro naṃ devaputtā paṭiggahetvā mātu purato ṭhapenti: ‘attamanā, devi, hohi; mahesakkho te putto uppanno’ti. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, before he reaches the ground, four gods receive him and place him before his mother, saying: ‘Rejoice, O Queen! An illustrious child is born to you.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.26.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (12) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.27, pts-vp-pli2.15, sc45
#. VAR: udena → uddena (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | udarena (katthaci)
#. VAR: asucinā suddho → visuddho (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:1.27.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova nikkhamati amakkhito udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito kenaci asucinā suddho visado. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any other kind of impurity, pure and clean. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.27.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, maṇiratanaṃ kāsike vatthe nikkhittaṃ neva maṇiratanaṃ kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ makkheti, nāpi kāsikaṃ vatthaṃ maṇiratanaṃ makkheti. "
msgstr "Suppose a jewel-treasure was placed on a cloth from Kāsī. The jewel would not soil the cloth, nor would the cloth soil the jewel. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.27.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn14:1.27.4"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ suddhattā. "
msgstr "Because of the cleanliness of them both. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:1.27.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, visadova nikkhamati amakkhito, udena amakkhito semhena amakkhito ruhirena amakkhito kenaci asucinā suddho visado. "
msgstr "In the same way, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, he emerges already clean, unsoiled by waters, mucus, blood, or any other kind of impurity, pure and clean. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.27.6"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (13) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.28, sc46
msgctxt "dn14:1.28.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, dve udakassa dhārā antalikkhā pātubhavanti—ekā sītassa ekā uṇhassa yena bodhisattassa udakakiccaṃ karonti mātu ca. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, two streams of water appear in the sky, one cool, one warm, for bathing the being intent on awakening and his mother. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.28.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (14) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.29, sc47
#. VAR: uttarābhimukho → uttare­nābhi­mukho (s1-3, km) uttarenamukho (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:1.29.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, sampatijāto bodhisatto samehi pādehi patiṭṭhahitvā uttarābhimukho sattapadavītihārena gacchati setamhi chatte anudhāriyamāne, sabbā ca disā anuviloketi, āsabhiṃ vācaṃ bhāsati ‘aggohamasmi lokassa, jeṭṭhohamasmi lokassa, seṭṭhohamasmi lokassa, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, as soon as he’s born, the being intent on awakening stands firm with his own feet on the ground. Facing north, he takes seven strides with a white parasol held above him, surveys all quarters, and makes this dramatic statement: ‘I am the foremost in the world! I am the eldest in the world! I am the best in the world! This is my last rebirth. Now there are no more future lives.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.29.2"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (15) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.30, sc48
msgctxt "dn14:1.30.1"
msgid "Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, yadā bodhisatto mātukucchimhā nikkhamati, atha sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati, atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s normal that, when the being intent on awakening emerges from his mother’s womb, then—in this world with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.30.2"
msgid "Yāpi tā lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā, yatthapime candimasūriyā evaṃmahiddhikā evaṃmahānubhāvā ābhāya nānubhonti, tatthapi appamāṇo uḷāro obhāso pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "Even in the boundless desolation of interstellar space—so utterly dark that even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, makes no impression—an immeasurable, magnificent light appears, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.30.3"
msgid "Yepi tattha sattā upapannā, tepi tenobhāsena aññamaññaṃ sañjānanti: ‘aññepi kira, bho, santi sattā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr "And the sentient beings reborn there recognize each other by that light: ‘So, it seems other sentient beings have been reborn here!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.30.4"
msgid "Ayañca dasasahassī lokadhātu saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati appamāṇo ca uḷāro obhāso loke pātubhavati atikkammeva devānaṃ devānubhāvaṃ. "
msgstr "And this galaxy shakes and rocks and trembles. And an immeasurable, magnificent light appears in the world, surpassing the glory of the gods. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.30.5"
msgid "Ayamettha dhammatā. (16) "
msgstr "This is normal in such a case. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:1.30.6"
msgid "3. Dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇā "
msgstr "3. The Thirty-Two Marks of a Great Man "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.31, pts-vp-pli2.16, sc49
msgctxt "dn14:1.31.1"
msgid "Jāte kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassimhi kumāre bandhumato rañño paṭivedesuṃ: "
msgstr "When Prince Vipassī was born, they announced it to King Bandhumata, "

#. VAR: deva → deva te (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:1.31.2"
msgid "‘putto te, deva, jāto, taṃ devo passatū’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sire, your son is born! Let your majesty examine him!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.3"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassiṃ kumāraṃ, disvā nemitte brāhmaṇe āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the king had examined the prince, he had the brahmin soothsayers summoned and said to them, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.4"
msgid "‘passantu bhonto nemittā brāhmaṇā kumāran’ti. "
msgstr "‘Gentlemen, please examine the prince.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.5"
msgid "Addasaṃsu kho, bhikkhave, nemittā brāhmaṇā vipassiṃ kumāraṃ, disvā bandhumantaṃ rājānaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When they had examined him they said to the king, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.6"
msgid "‘attamano, deva, hohi, mahesakkho te putto uppanno, lābhā te, mahārāja, suladdhaṃ te, mahārāja, yassa te kule evarūpo putto uppanno. "
msgstr "‘Rejoice, O King! An illustrious son is born to you. You are fortunate, so very fortunate, to have a son such as this born in this family!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.7"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato, yehi samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā. "
msgstr "For the prince has the thirty-two marks of a great man. A great man who possesses these has only two possible destinies, no other. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.8"
msgid "Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr "If he stays at home he becomes a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion extends to all four sides, he achieves stability in the country, and he possesses the seven treasures. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.9"
msgid "Tassimāni sattaratanāni bhavanti. "
msgstr "He has the following seven treasures: "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.10"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr "the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.11"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr "He has over a thousand sons who are valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of his enemies. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.12"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasati. "
msgstr "After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigns by principle, without rod or sword. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.31.13"
msgid "Sace kho pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke vivaṭacchado. "
msgstr "But if he goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, he becomes a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.32, pts-vp-pli2.17, sc50
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.1"
msgid "Katamehi cāyaṃ, deva, kumāro dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato, yehi samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā. "
msgstr "And what are the marks which he possesses? "

msgctxt "dn14:1.32.2"
msgid "Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.32.3"
msgid "Tassimāni sattaratanāni bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.32.4"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.32.5"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.32.6"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasati. "
msgstr "After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigns by principle, without rod or sword. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.7"
msgid "Sace kho pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke vivaṭacchado. Ayañhi, deva, kumāro suppatiṭṭhitapādo. Yaṃ pāyaṃ, deva, kumāro suppatiṭṭhitapādo. Idampissa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (1) "
msgstr "He has well-planted feet. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
#. VAR: Imassa, deva → imassa hi deva (?)
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.8"
msgid "Imassa, deva, kumārassa heṭṭhā pādatalesu cakkāni jātāni sahassārāni sanemikāni sanābhikāni sabbākāraparipūrāni. Yampi imassa, deva, kumārassa heṭṭhā pādatalesu cakkāni jātāni sahassārāni sanemikāni sanābhikāni sabbākāraparipūrāni, idampissa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (2) "
msgstr "On the soles of his feet there are thousand-spoked wheels, with rims and hubs, complete in every detail. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.9"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro āyatapaṇhī … pe … (3) "
msgstr "He has projecting heels. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.10"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro dīghaṅgulī … pe … (4) "
msgstr "He has long fingers. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc55
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.11"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro mudutalunahatthapādo … pe … (5) "
msgstr "His hands and feet are tender. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc56
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.12"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva kumāro jālahatthapādo … pe … (6) "
msgstr "His hands and feet cling gracefully. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc57
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.13"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro ussaṅkhapādo … pe … (7) "
msgstr "His feet are arched. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc58
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.14"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro eṇijaṅgho … pe … (8) "
msgstr "His calves are like those of an antelope. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc59
#. VAR: parimasati → parāmasati (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.15"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro ṭhitakova anonamanto ubhohi pāṇitalehi jaṇṇukāni parimasati parimajjati … pe … (9) "
msgstr "When standing upright and not bending over, the palms of both hands touch the knees. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc60
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.16"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro kosohitavatthaguyho … pe … (10) "
msgstr "His private parts are retracted. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc61
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.17"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro suvaṇṇavaṇṇo kañcanasannibhattaco … pe … (11) "
msgstr "He is gold colored; his skin has a golden sheen. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.18, sc62
#. VAR: upalimpati → upalippati (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.18"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro sukhumacchavī; sukhumattā chaviyā rajojallaṃ kāye na upalimpati … pe … (12) "
msgstr "He has delicate skin, so delicate that dust and dirt don’t stick to his body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc63
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.19"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro ekekalomo; ekekāni lomāni lomakūpesu jātāni … pe … (13) "
msgstr "His hairs grow one per pore. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc64
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.20"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro uddhaggalomo; uddhaggāni lomāni jātāni nīlāni añjanavaṇṇāni kuṇḍalāvaṭṭāni dakkhiṇāvaṭṭakajātāni … pe … (14) "
msgstr "His hairs stand up; they’re blue-black and curl clockwise. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc65
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.21"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro brahmujugatto … pe … (15) "
msgstr "His body is as straight as Brahmā’s. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc66
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.22"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro sattussado … pe … (16) "
msgstr "He has bulging muscles in seven places. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc67
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.23"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro sīhapubbaddhakāyo … pe … (17) "
msgstr "His chest is like that of a lion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc68
#. VAR: citantaraṃso → pittantaraṃso (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.24"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro citantaraṃso … pe … (18) "
msgstr "The gap between the shoulder-blades is filled in. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc69
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.25"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro nigrodhaparimaṇḍalo yāvatakvassa kāyo tāvatakvassa byāmo, yāvatakvassa byāmo, tāvatakvassa kāyo … pe … (19) "
msgstr "He has the proportional circumference of a banyan tree: the span of his arms equals the height of his body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc70
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.26"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro samavaṭṭakkhandho … pe … (20) "
msgstr "His torso is cylindrical. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc71
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.27"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro rasaggasaggī … pe … (21) "
msgstr "He has an excellent sense of taste. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc72
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.28"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro sīhahanu … pe … (22) "
msgstr "His jaw is like that of a lion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc73
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.29"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro cattālīsadanto … pe … (23) "
msgstr "He has forty teeth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc74
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.30"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro samadanto … pe … (24) "
msgstr "His teeth are even. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc75
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.31"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro aviraḷadanto … pe … (25) "
msgstr "His teeth have no gaps. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc76
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.32"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro susukkadāṭho … pe … (26) "
msgstr "His teeth are perfectly white. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc77
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.33"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro pahūtajivho … pe … (27) "
msgstr "He has a large tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc78
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.34"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro brahmassaro karavīkabhāṇī … pe … (28) "
msgstr "He has the voice of Brahmā, like a cuckoo’s call. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc79
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.35"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro abhinīlanetto … pe … (29) "
msgstr "His eyes are deep blue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc80
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.36"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro gopakhumo … pe … (30) "
msgstr "He has eyelashes like a cow’s. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.19, sc81
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.37"
msgid "Imassa, deva, kumārassa uṇṇā bhamukantare jātā odātā mudutūlasannibhā. Yampi imassa, deva, kumārassa uṇṇā bhamukantare jātā odātā mudutūlasannibhā, idampimassa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (31) "
msgstr "Between his eyebrows there grows a tuft, soft and white like cotton-wool. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc82
msgctxt "dn14:1.32.38"
msgid "Ayañhi, deva, kumāro uṇhīsasīso. Yaṃ pāyaṃ, deva, kumāro uṇhīsasīso, idampissa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (32) "
msgstr "His head is shaped like a turban. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.33, sc83
msgctxt "dn14:1.33.1"
msgid "Imehi kho ayaṃ, deva, kumāro dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato, yehi samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā. "
msgstr "These are the thirty-two marks of a great man that the prince has. A great man who possesses these has only two possible destinies, no other. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.33.2"
msgid "Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr "If he stays at home he becomes a king, a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.33.3"
msgid "Tassimāni sattaratanāni bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.33.4"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.33.5"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: asatthena dhammena → dhammena samena (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.33.6"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.33.7"
msgid "Sace kho pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke vivaṭacchado’ti. "
msgstr "But if he goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, he becomes a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the world.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:1.33.8"
msgid "4. Vipassīsamaññā "
msgstr "4. How He Came to be Known as Vipassī "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.20, sc84
#. VAR: acchādāpetvā → acchādetvā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.33.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā nemitte brāhmaṇe ahatehi vatthehi acchādāpetvā sabbakāmehi santappesi. "
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma had the brahmin soothsayers dressed in fresh clothes and satisfied all their needs. "

#. REF: pts-cs1.34
msgctxt "dn14:1.34.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa dhātiyo upaṭṭhāpesi. "
msgstr "Then the king appointed nurses for Prince Vipassī. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.2"
msgid "Aññā khīraṃ pāyenti, aññā nhāpenti, aññā dhārenti, aññā aṅkena pariharanti. "
msgstr "Some suckled him, some bathed him, some held him, and some carried him on their hip. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.3"
msgid "Jātassa kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa setacchattaṃ dhārayittha divā ceva rattiñca: "
msgstr "From when he was born, a white parasol was held over him night and day, with the thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.4"
msgid "‘mā naṃ sītaṃ vā uṇhaṃ vā tiṇaṃ vā rajo vā ussāvo vā bādhayitthā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Don’t let cold, heat, grass, dust, or damp bother him.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.5"
msgid "Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahuno janassa piyo ahosi manāpo. "
msgstr "He was dear and beloved by many people, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā bahuno janassa piyaṃ manāpaṃ; "
msgstr "like a blue water lily, or a pink or white lotus. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.7"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahuno janassa piyo ahosi manāpo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:1.34.8"
msgid "Svāssudaṃ aṅkeneva aṅkaṃ parihariyati. "
msgstr "He was always passed from hip to hip. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.35, sc85
#. VAR: kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca → kumāro brahmassaro mañjussaro ca (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:1.35.1"
msgid "Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca ahosi vaggussaro ca madhurassaro ca pemaniyassaro ca. "
msgstr "From when he was born, his voice was charming, graceful, sweet, and lovely. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.35.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, himavante pabbate karavīkā nāma sakuṇajāti mañjussarā ca vaggussarā ca madhurassarā ca pemaniyassarā ca; "
msgstr "It was as sweet as the song of a cuckoo-bird found in the Himalayas. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.35.3"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro mañjussaro ca ahosi vaggussaro ca madhurassaro ca pemaniyassaro ca. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.36, sc86
#. VAR: yena sudaṃ → yena dūraṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.36.1"
msgid "Jātassa kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa kammavipākajaṃ dibbacakkhu pāturahosi yena sudaṃ samantā yojanaṃ passati divā ceva rattiñca. "
msgstr "From when he was born, Prince Vipassī had the power of clairvoyance which manifested as a result of past deeds. He could see for a league all around both by day and by night. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.37, sc87
msgctxt "dn14:1.37.1"
msgid "Jāto kho pana, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro animisanto pekkhati seyyathāpi devā tāvatiṃsā. "
msgstr "And he was unblinkingly watchful, like the gods of the Thirty-Three. "

#. VAR: Animisanto kumāro pekkhatī’ti kho, bhikkhave → jātassa kho pana bhikkhave (s1-3) | animmissantā pekkhāti evameva kho bhikkheve (km) | jātassa kho pana bhikkhave (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:1.37.2"
msgid "‘Animisanto kumāro pekkhatī’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa ‘vipassī vipassī’ tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "And because it was said that he was unblinkingly watchful, he came to be known as ‘Vipassī’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.21, sc88
#. VAR: atthakaraṇe → aṭṭakaraṇe (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.37.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā atthakaraṇe nisinno vipassiṃ kumāraṃ aṅke nisīdāpetvā atthe anusāsati. "
msgstr "Then while King Bandhuma was sitting in judgment, he’d sit Prince Vipassī in his lap and explain the case to him. "

# NOTE: MW is wrong here.
#. VAR: ñāyena → ñāṇena (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:1.37.4"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro pituaṅke nisinno viceyya viceyya atthe panāyati ñāyena. "
msgstr "And sitting there in his father’s lap, Vipassī would thoroughly consider the case and draw a conclusion using a logical procedure. "

msgctxt "dn14:1.37.5"
msgid "Viceyya viceyya kumāro atthe panāyati ñāyenāti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa kumārassa bhiyyoso mattāya ‘vipassī vipassī’ tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "So this was all the more reason for him to be known as ‘Vipassī’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs1.38, sc89
msgctxt "dn14:1.38.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa tayo pāsāde kārāpesi, ekaṃ vassikaṃ ekaṃ hemantikaṃ ekaṃ gimhikaṃ; "
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma had three stilt longhouses built for him—one for the winter, one for the summer, and one for the rainy season, "

msgctxt "dn14:1.38.2"
msgid "pañca kāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpesi. "
msgstr "and provided him with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

#. VAR: Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro vassike pāsāde cattāro māse → vassike pāsāde vassike cattāro māse (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:1.38.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro vassike pāsāde cattāro māse nippurisehi tūriyehi paricārayamāno na heṭṭhāpāsādaṃ orohatīti. "
msgstr "Prince Vipassī stayed in a stilt longhouse without coming downstairs for the four months of the rainy season, where he was entertained by musicians—none of them men. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn14:1.38.4"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:1.38.5"
msgid "5. Jiṇṇapurisa "
msgstr "5. The Old Man "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.1, sc90
msgctxt "dn14:2.1.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after many thousand years had passed, Prince Vipassī addressed his charioteer, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.1.2"
msgid "‘yojehi, samma sārathi, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmidassanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, harness the finest chariots. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.1.3"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojetvā vipassissa kumārassa paṭivedesi: "
msgstr "‘Yes, sir,’ replied the charioteer. He harnessed the chariots and informed the prince, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.1.4"
msgid "‘yuttāni kho te, deva, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, "
msgstr "‘Sire, the finest chariots are harnessed. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.1.5"
msgid "yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti. "
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.’ "

#. VAR: bhaddaṃ yānaṃ → bhadraṃ yānaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:2.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyāsi. "
msgstr "Then Prince Vipassī mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out for the park. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.2, pts-vp-pli2.22, sc91
#. VAR: bhoggaṃ → bhaggaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.1"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto purisaṃ jiṇṇaṃ gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ daṇḍaparāyanaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantaṃ āturaṃ gatayobbanaṃ. "
msgstr "Along the way he saw an elderly man, bent double, crooked, leaning on a staff, trembling as he walked, ailing, past his prime. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.2.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.2.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pana, samma sārathi, puriso kiṃkato? "
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, what has that man done? "

msgctxt "dn14:2.2.4"
msgid "Kesāpissa na yathā aññesaṃ, kāyopissa na yathā aññesan’ti. "
msgstr "For his hair and his body are unlike those of other men.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.5"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, jiṇṇo nāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That, Your Majesty, is called an old man.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.6"
msgid "‘Kiṃ paneso, samma sārathi, jiṇṇo nāmā’ti? "
msgstr "‘But why is he called an old man?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.7"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, jiṇṇo nāma. Na dāni tena ciraṃ jīvitabbaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘He’s called an old man because now he has not long to live.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.8"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, ahampi jarādhammo, jaraṃ anatīto’ti? "
msgstr "‘But my dear charioteer, am I liable to grow old? Am I not exempt from old age?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.9"
msgid "‘Tvañca, deva, mayañcamha sabbe jarādhammā, jaraṃ anatītā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Everyone is liable to grow old, Your Majesty, including you. No-one is exempt from old age.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.10"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma sārathi, alaṃ dānajja uyyānabhūmiyā. Itova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, my dear charioteer, that’s enough of the park for today. Let’s return to the royal compound.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.11"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the charioteer and did so. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.2.12"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro antepuraṃ gato dukkhī dummano pajjhāyati: "
msgstr "Back at the royal compound, the prince brooded, miserable and sad: "

msgctxt "dn14:2.2.13"
msgid "‘dhiratthu kira, bho, jāti nāma, yatra hi nāma jātassa jarā paññāyissatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Damn this thing called rebirth, since old age will come to anyone who’s born.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.3, pts-vp-pli2.23, sc92
msgctxt "dn14:2.3.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā sārathiṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma summoned the charioteer and said, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.3.2"
msgid "‘kacci, samma sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha? Kacci, samma sārathi, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti? "
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, I hope the prince enjoyed himself at the park? I hope he was happy there?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.3.3"
msgid "‘Na kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā abhiramittha, na kho, deva, kumāro uyyānabhūmiyā attamano ahosī’ti. "
msgstr "‘No, Your Majesty, the prince didn’t enjoy himself at the park.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.3.4"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, samma sārathi, addasa kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto’ti? "
msgstr "‘But what did he see on the way to the park?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.3.5"
