msgstr "Along the way he saw a man who was ill, suffering, gravely ill, collapsed in his own urine and feces, being picked up by some and put down by others. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.6.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.6.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pana, samma sārathi, puriso kiṃkato? "
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, what has that man done? "

#. VAR: saropissa → siropissa (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:2.6.4"
msgid "Akkhīnipissa na yathā aññesaṃ, saropissa na yathā aññesan’ti? "
msgstr "For his eyes and his voice are unlike those of other men.’ "

