msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.11.21"
msgid "“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho ahaṃ, deva, vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.11.22"
msgid "So kho, deva, kumāro antepuraṃ gato dukkhī dummano pajjhāyati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.11.23"
msgid "“dhiratthu kira, bho, jāti nāma, yatra hi nāma jātassa jarā paññāyissati, byādhi paññāyissati, maraṇaṃ paññāyissatī”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:2.11.24"
msgid "8. Pabbajita "
msgstr "8. The Renunciate "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.12, pts-vp-pli2.28, sc103
msgctxt "dn14:2.12.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumassa rañño etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then King Bandhuma thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.12.2"
msgid "‘mā heva kho vipassī kumāro na rajjaṃ kāresi, mā heva vipassī kumāro agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji, mā heva nemittānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ assa vacanan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Prince Vipassī must not renounce the throne. He must not go forth from the lay life to homelessness. And the words of the brahmin soothsayers must not come true.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.12.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bandhumā rājā vipassissa kumārassa bhiyyoso mattāya pañca kāmaguṇāni upaṭṭhāpesi: "
msgstr "To this end he provided the prince with even more of the five kinds of sensual stimulation, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.12.4"
msgid "‘yathā vipassī kumāro rajjaṃ kareyya, yathā vipassī kumāro na agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyya, yathā nemittānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ micchā assa vacanan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: pts-cs2.13, sc104
msgctxt "dn14:2.13.1"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti. "
msgstr "with which the prince amused himself. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.13.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after many thousand years had passed, Prince Vipassī had his charioteer drive him to the park once more. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.13.3"
msgid "‘yojehi, samma sārathi, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmidassanāyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.13.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojetvā vipassissa kumārassa paṭivedesi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.13.5"
msgid "‘yuttāni kho te, deva, bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.13.6"
msgid "yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:2.13.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyāsi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.14, pts-vp-pli2.29, sc105
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.1"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanto purisaṃ bhaṇḍuṃ pabbajitaṃ kāsāyavasanaṃ. "
msgstr "Along the way he saw a man, a renunciate with shaven head, wearing an ocher robe. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.2"
msgid "Disvā sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "He addressed his charioteer, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pana, samma sārathi, puriso kiṃkato? "
msgstr "‘My dear charioteer, what has that man done? "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.4"
msgid "Sīsampissa na yathā aññesaṃ, vatthānipissa na yathā aññesan’ti? "
msgstr "For his head and his clothes are unlike those of other men.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.5"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, pabbajito nāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That, Your Majesty, is called a renunciate.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.6"
msgid "‘Kiṃ paneso, samma sārathi, pabbajito nāmā’ti? "
msgstr "‘But why is he called a renunciate?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: samacariyā → sammacariyā (mr)
#. VAR: kusalakiriyā → kusalacariyā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.7"
msgid "‘Eso kho, deva, pabbajito nāma sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti. "
msgstr "‘He is called a renunciate because he celebrates principled and fair conduct, skillful actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for living creatures.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.8"
msgid "‘Sādhu kho so, samma sārathi, pabbajito nāma, sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā. "
msgstr "‘Then I celebrate the one called a renunciate, who celebrates principled and fair conduct, skillful actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for living creatures! "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.9"
msgid "Tena hi, samma sārathi, yena so pabbajito tena rathaṃ pesehī’ti. "
msgstr "Well then, drive the chariot up to that renunciate.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.10"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā yena so pabbajito tena rathaṃ pesesi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the charioteer, and did so. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro taṃ pabbajitaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Prince Vipassī said to that renunciate, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.12"
msgid "‘tvaṃ pana, samma, kiṃkato, "
msgstr "‘My good man, what have you done? "

msgctxt "dn14:2.14.13"
msgid "sīsampi te na yathā aññesaṃ, vatthānipi te na yathā aññesan’ti? "
msgstr "For your head and your clothes are unlike those of other men.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.14"
msgid "‘Ahaṃ kho, deva, pabbajito nāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sire, I am what is called a renunciate.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.15"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, samma, pabbajito nāmā’ti? "
msgstr "‘But why are you called a renunciate?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.16"
msgid "‘Ahaṃ kho, deva, pabbajito nāma, sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti. "
msgstr "‘I am called a renunciate because I celebrate principled and fair conduct, skillful actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for living creatures.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.17"
msgid "‘Sādhu kho tvaṃ, samma, pabbajito nāma sādhu dhammacariyā sādhu samacariyā sādhu kusalakiriyā sādhu puññakiriyā sādhu avihiṃsā sādhu bhūtānukampā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Then I celebrate the one called a renunciate, who celebrates principled and fair conduct, skillful actions, good deeds, harmlessness, and compassion for living creatures!’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:2.14.18"
msgid "9. Bodhisattapabbajjā "
msgstr "9. The Going Forth "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.15, sc106
msgctxt "dn14:2.15.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī kumāro sārathiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the prince addressed the charioteer, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.15.2"
msgid "‘tena hi, samma sārathi, rathaṃ ādāya itova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāhi. "
msgstr "‘Well then, my dear charioteer, take the chariot and return to the royal compound. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.15.3"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana idheva kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I shall shave off my hair and beard right here, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.15.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, sārathi vipassissa kumārassa paṭissutvā rathaṃ ādāya tatova antepuraṃ paccaniyyāsi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the charioteer and did so. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:2.15.5"
msgid "Vipassī pana kumāro tattheva kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji. "
msgstr "Then Prince Vipassī shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:2.15.6"
msgid "10. Mahājanakāyaanupabbajjā "
msgstr "10. A Great Crowd Goes Forth "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.16, pts-vp-pli2.30, sc107
msgctxt "dn14:2.16.1"
msgid "Assosi kho, bhikkhave, bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni: "
msgstr "A large crowd of 84,000 people in the capital of Bandhumatī heard "

msgctxt "dn14:2.16.2"
msgid "‘vipassī kira kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito’ti. "
msgstr "that Vipassī had gone forth. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.16.3"
msgid "Sutvāna tesaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to them, "

#. VAR: orakā → orikā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:2.16.4"
msgid "‘na hi nūna so orako dhammavinayo, na sā orakā pabbajjā, yattha vipassī kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito. "
msgstr "‘This must be no ordinary teaching and training, no ordinary going forth in which Prince Vipassī has gone forth. "

#. VAR: pana mayan’ti → pana na mayanti (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: kimaṅgaṃ → kimaṅga (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:2.16.5"
msgid "Vipassīpi nāma kumāro kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissati, kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti. "
msgstr "If even the prince goes forth, why don’t we do the same?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc108
#. VAR: mahājanakāyo → mahājanakāyā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:2.16.6"
msgid "Atha kho, so bhikkhave, mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā vipassiṃ bodhisattaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitaṃ anupabbajiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then that great crowd of 84,000 people shaved off their hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and followed the one intent on awakening, Vipassī, by going forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

# NOTE: Following PTS in omitting janapada, which seems out of place here, and is absent from the parallel passage in DN 19.
msgctxt "dn14:2.16.7"
msgid "Tāya sudaṃ, bhikkhave, parisāya parivuto vipassī bodhisatto gāmanigamajanapadarājadhānīsu cārikaṃ carati. "
msgstr "Escorted by that assembly, Vipassī wandered on tour among the villages, towns, and capital cities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.17, sc109
msgctxt "dn14:2.17.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

#. VAR: na kho metaṃ → na kho panetaṃ (s1-3, km) | na kho me taṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:2.17.2"
msgid "‘na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ ākiṇṇo viharāmi, yannūnāhaṃ eko gaṇamhā vūpakaṭṭho vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘It’s not appropriate for me to live in a crowd. Why don’t I live alone, withdrawn from the group?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.17.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto aparena samayena eko gaṇamhā vūpakaṭṭho vihāsi, aññeneva tāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni agamaṃsu, aññena maggena vipassī bodhisatto. "
msgstr "After some time he withdrew from the group to live alone. The 84,000 went one way, but Vipassī went another. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:2.17.4"
msgid "11. Bodhisattaabhinivesa "
msgstr "11. Vipassī’s Reflections "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.18, pts-vp-pli2.31, sc110
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa vāsūpagatassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

#. VAR: jīyati ca mīyati ca → jiyyati ca miyyati ca (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.2"
msgid "‘kicchaṃ vatāyaṃ loko āpanno, jāyati ca jīyati ca mīyati ca cavati ca upapajjati ca, atha ca panimassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ nappajānāti jarāmaraṇassa, "
msgstr "‘Alas, this world has fallen into trouble. It’s born, grows old, dies, passes away, and is reborn, yet it doesn’t understand how to escape from this suffering, from old age and death. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.3"
msgid "kudāssu nāma imassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ paññāyissati jarāmaraṇassā’ti? "
msgstr "Oh, when will an escape be found from this suffering, from old age and death?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc111
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.5"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there old age and death? What is a condition for old age and death?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.6"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.7"
msgid "‘jātiyā kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti. "
msgstr "‘When rebirth exists there’s old age and death. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc112
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.9"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jāti hoti, kiṃpaccayā jātī’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there rebirth? What is a condition for rebirth?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.10"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.11"
msgid "‘bhave kho sati jāti hoti, bhavapaccayā jātī’ti. "
msgstr "‘When continued existence exists there’s rebirth. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc113
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.12"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.13"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati bhavo hoti, kiṃpaccayā bhavo’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there continued existence? What is a condition for continued existence?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.14"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.15"
msgid "‘upādāne kho sati bhavo hoti, upādānapaccayā bhavo’ti. "
msgstr "‘When grasping exists there’s continued existence. Grasping is a condition for continued existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc114
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.16"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.17"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati upādānaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā upādānan’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there grasping? What is a condition for grasping?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.18"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.19"
msgid "‘taṇhāya kho sati upādānaṃ hoti, taṇhāpaccayā upādānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘When craving exists there’s grasping. Craving is a condition for grasping.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc115
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.20"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.21"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati taṇhā hoti, kiṃpaccayā taṇhā’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there craving? What is a condition for craving?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.22"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.23"
msgid "‘vedanāya kho sati taṇhā hoti, vedanāpaccayā taṇhā’ti. "
msgstr "‘When feeling exists there’s craving. Feeling is a condition for craving.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.32, sc116
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.24"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.25"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati vedanā hoti, kiṃpaccayā vedanā’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there feeling? What is a condition for feeling?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.26"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.27"
msgid "‘phasse kho sati vedanā hoti, phassapaccayā vedanā’ti. "
msgstr "‘When contact exists there’s feeling. Contact is a condition for feeling.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc117
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.28"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.29"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati phasso hoti, kiṃpaccayā phasso’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there contact? What is a condition for contact?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.30"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.31"
msgid "‘saḷāyatane kho sati phasso hoti, saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso’ti. "
msgstr "‘When the six sense fields exist there’s contact. The six sense fields are a condition for contact.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc118
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.32"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.33"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā saḷāyatanan’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists are there the six sense fields? What is a condition for the six sense fields?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.34"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.35"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti, nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanan’ti. "
msgstr "‘When name and form exist there are the six sense fields. Name and form are a condition for the six sense fields.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc119
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.36"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.37"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā nāmarūpan’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists are there name and form? What is a condition for name and form?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.38"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.39"
msgid "‘viññāṇe kho sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan’ti. "
msgstr "‘When consciousness exists there are name and form. Consciousness is a condition for name and form.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc120
msgctxt "dn14:2.18.40"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.41"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā viññāṇan’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what exists is there consciousness? What is a condition for consciousness?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.42"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.18.43"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇan’ti. "
msgstr "‘When name and form exist there’s consciousness. Name and form are a condition for consciousness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.19, pts-vp-pli2.33, sc121
msgctxt "dn14:2.19.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.19.2"
msgid "‘paccudāvattati kho idaṃ viññāṇaṃ nāmarūpamhā, nāparaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "‘This consciousness turns back from name and form, and doesn’t go beyond that.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.19.3"
msgid "Ettāvatā jāyetha vā jiyyetha vā miyyetha vā cavetha vā upapajjetha vā, yadidaṃ "
msgstr "It is to this extent that one may be reborn, grow old, die, pass away, or reappear. That is: "

msgctxt "dn14:2.19.4"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ, nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ, saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, vedanāpaccayā taṇhā, taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ, upādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Name and form are conditions for consciousness. Consciousness is a condition for name and form. Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields. The six sense fields are conditions for contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. Feeling is a condition for craving. Craving is a condition for grasping. Grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.19.5"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti’. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc122
msgctxt "dn14:2.19.6"
msgid "‘Samudayo samudayo’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu cakkhuṃ udapādi, ñāṇaṃ udapādi, paññā udapādi, vijjā udapādi, āloko udapādi. "
msgstr "‘Origination, origination.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, realization, and light that arose in Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, regarding teachings not learned before from another. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.20, sc123
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no old age and death? When what ceases do old age and death cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.4"
msgid "‘jātiyā kho asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When rebirth doesn’t exist there’s no old age and death. When rebirth ceases, old age and death cease.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc124
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.6"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati jāti na hoti, kissa nirodhā jātinirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no rebirth? When what ceases does rebirth cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.8"
msgid "‘bhave kho asati jāti na hoti, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When continued existence doesn’t exist there’s no rebirth. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc125
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.10"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati bhavo na hoti, kissa nirodhā bhavanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no continued existence? When what ceases does continued existence cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.12"
msgid "‘upādāne kho asati bhavo na hoti, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When grasping doesn’t exist there’s no continued existence. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc126
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.13"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.14"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati upādānaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā upādānanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no grasping? When what ceases does grasping cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.15"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.16"
msgid "‘taṇhāya kho asati upādānaṃ na hoti, taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When craving doesn’t exist there’s no grasping. When craving ceases, grasping ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.34, sc127
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.17"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.18"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati taṇhā na hoti, kissa nirodhā taṇhānirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no craving? When what ceases does craving cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.19"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.20"
msgid "‘vedanāya kho asati taṇhā na hoti, vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When feeling doesn’t exist there’s no craving. When feeling ceases, craving ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc128
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.21"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.22"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati vedanā na hoti, kissa nirodhā vedanānirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no feeling? When what ceases does feeling cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.23"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.24"
msgid "‘phasse kho asati vedanā na hoti, phassanirodhā vedanānirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When contact doesn’t exist there’s no feeling. When contact ceases, feeling ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc129
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.25"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.26"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati phasso na hoti, kissa nirodhā phassanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no contact? When what ceases does contact cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.27"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.28"
msgid "‘saḷāyatane kho asati phasso na hoti, saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When the six sense fields don’t exist there’s no contact. When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc130
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.29"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.30"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati saḷāyatanaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā saḷāyatananirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist are there no six sense fields? When what ceases do the six sense fields cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.31"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.32"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho asati saḷāyatanaṃ na hoti, nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When name and form don’t exist there are no six sense fields. When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc131
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.33"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.34"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati nāmarūpaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā nāmarūpanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist are there no name and form? When what ceases do name and form cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.35"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.36"
msgid "‘viññāṇe kho asati nāmarūpaṃ na hoti, viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When consciousness doesn’t exist there are no name and form. When consciousness ceases, name and form cease.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc132
msgctxt "dn14:2.20.37"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.38"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā viññāṇanirodho’ti? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no consciousness? When what ceases does consciousness cease?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.39"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo: "
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, Vipassī comprehended with wisdom, "

msgctxt "dn14:2.20.40"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti, nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho’ti. "
msgstr "‘When name and form don’t exist there’s no consciousness. When name and form cease, consciousness ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.21, pts-vp-pli2.35, sc133
msgctxt "dn14:2.21.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Vipassī thought, "

# NOTE: The PTS’s inclusion of vipassana here, unaccountably followed by RD and MW, is an egregious and embarassing error. No manuscript contains this reading, and the PTS edition itself states that the word is found only in the commentary. To be clear, there it is obviously presented not as a reading but as an explanation: “Maggoti vipassanāmaggo.”
msgctxt "dn14:2.21.2"
msgid "‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ maggo sambodhāya yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘I have discovered the path to awakening. That is: "

msgctxt "dn14:2.21.3"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho, viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho, nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho, saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho, phassanirodhā vedanānirodho, vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho, taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When name and form cease, consciousness ceases. When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease. When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. When contact ceases, feeling ceases. When feeling ceases, craving ceases. When craving ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.21.4"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti’. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc134
msgctxt "dn14:2.21.5"
msgid "‘Nirodho nirodho’ti kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bodhisattassa pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu cakkhuṃ udapādi, ñāṇaṃ udapādi, paññā udapādi, vijjā udapādi, āloko udapādi. "
msgstr "‘Cessation, cessation.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, realization, and light that arose in Vipassī, the one intent on awakening, regarding teachings not learned before from another. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.22, sc135
msgctxt "dn14:2.22.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bodhisatto aparena samayena pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī vihāsi: "
msgstr "Some time later Vipassī meditated observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.2"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.3"
msgid "iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of feeling. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.4"
msgid "iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of perception. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.5"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of choices. "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.6"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti, "
msgstr "Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:2.22.7"
msgid "tassa pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassino viharato na cirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccīti. "
msgstr "Meditating like this his mind was soon freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn14:2.22.8"
msgid "Dutiyabhāṇavāro. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:2.22.9"
msgid "12. Brahmayācanakathā "
msgstr "12. The Appeal of Brahmā "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.1, pts-vp-pli2.36, sc136
msgctxt "dn14:3.1.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I teach the Dhamma?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.4"
msgid "‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo. "
msgstr "‘This principle I have discovered is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.5"
msgid "Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā. "
msgstr "But people like attachment, they love it and enjoy it. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.6"
msgid "Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo. "
msgstr "It’s hard for them to see this thing; that is, specific conditionality, dependent origination. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.7"
msgid "Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s also hard for them to see this thing; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.1.8"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ; so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā’ti. "
msgstr "And if I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would be wearying and troublesome for me.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.2, sc137
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.1"
msgid "Apissu, bhikkhave, vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā: "
msgstr "And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to him: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc138
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.2"
msgid "‘Kicchena me adhigataṃ, "
msgstr "‘I’ve struggled hard to realize this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.3"
msgid "halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ; "
msgstr "enough with trying to explain it! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.4"
msgid "Rāgadosaparetehi, "
msgstr "This teaching is not easily understood "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.5"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho. "
msgstr "by those mired in greed and hate. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc139
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.6"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Those caught up in greed can’t see "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.7"
msgid "gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ; "
msgstr "what’s subtle, going against the stream, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.8"
msgid "Rāgarattā na dakkhanti, "
msgstr "deep, hard to see, and very fine, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.9"
msgid "tamokhandhena āvuṭā’ti. "
msgstr "for they’re shrouded in a mass of darkness.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc140
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.10"
msgid "Itiha, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ nami, no dhammadesanāya. "
msgstr "So, as the Buddha Vipassī reflected like this, his mind inclined to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.37, sc141
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññatarassa mahābrahmuno vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then a certain Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, thought, "

#. VAR: namati → nami (s1-3, km, mr) | namissati (?)
msgctxt "dn14:3.2.12"
msgid "‘nassati vata bho loko, vinassati vata bho loko, yatra hi nāma vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati, no dhammadesanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh my goodness! The world will be lost, the world will perish! For the mind of the Realized One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, inclines to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.2.13"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha Vipassī. "

#. REF: pts-cs3.3
#. VAR: nihantvā → nidahanto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.3.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dakkhiṇaṃ jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ pathaviyaṃ nihantvā yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha Vipassī, and said, "

#. VAR: santi → santīdha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.3.2"
msgid "‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Sir, let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! Let the Holy One teach the Dhamma! "

msgctxt "dn14:3.3.3"
msgid "santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā; assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
msgstr "There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.3.4"
msgid "bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand the teaching!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.4, pts-vp-pli2.38, sc142
#. VAR: Evaṃ vutte → atha kho (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the Buddha Vipassī said to him, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.2"
msgid "‘mayhampi kho, brahme, etadahosi: "
msgstr "‘I too thought this, Brahmā, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.3"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“Why don’t I teach the Dhamma?” "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, brahme, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.5"
msgid "“adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.6"
msgid "Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.7"
msgid "Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.8"
msgid "Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.9"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ; so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā”ti. "
msgstr "“If I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would be wearying and troublesome for me.” "

msgctxt "dn14:3.4.10"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, brahme, imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc143
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.11"
msgid "“Kicchena me adhigataṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.12"
msgid "halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.13"
msgid "Rāgadosaparetehi, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.14"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc144
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.15"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.16"
msgid "gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.17"
msgid "Rāgarattā na dakkhanti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.18"
msgid "tamokhandhena āvuṭā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc145
msgctxt "dn14:3.4.19"
msgid "Itiha me, brahme, paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ nami, no dhammadesanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "So, as I reflected like this, my mind inclined to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.5, sc146
msgctxt "dn14:3.5.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā … pe … "
msgstr "For a second time, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.5.2"
msgid "tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and a third time that Great Brahmā begged the Buddha to teach. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.5.3"
msgid "‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ, santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.6, pts-vp-pli2.39, sc147
msgctxt "dn14:3.6.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho brahmuno ca ajjhesanaṃ viditvā sattesu ca kāruññataṃ paṭicca buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokesi. "
msgstr "Then, understanding Brahmā’s invitation, the Buddha Vipassī surveyed the world with the eye of a Buddha, because of his compassion for sentient beings. "

#. VAR: suviññāpaye duviññāpaye → duviññāpaye bhabbe abhabbe (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.6.2"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante. "
msgstr "And he saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes; with keen faculties and with weak faculties, with good qualities and with bad qualities, easy to teach and hard to teach. And some of them lived seeing the danger in the fault to do with the next world, while others did not. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.6.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni anto nimuggaposīni. Appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni samodakaṃ ṭhitāni. Appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakā accuggamma ṭhitāni anupalittāni udakena. "
msgstr "It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. Some of them sprout and grow in the water reaching the water’s surface. And some of them sprout and grow in the water but rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.6.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento addasa satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante. "
msgstr "In the same way, the Buddha Vipassī saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.7, sc148
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then that Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc149
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.2"
msgid "‘Sele yathā pabbatamuddhaniṭṭhito, "
msgstr "‘Standing high on a rocky mountain, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.3"
msgid "Yathāpi passe janataṃ samantato; "
msgstr "you can see the people all around. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.4"
msgid "Tathūpamaṃ dhammamayaṃ sumedha, "
msgstr "In just the same way, all-seer, wise one, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.5"
msgid "Pāsādamāruyha samantacakkhu; "
msgstr "ascend the palace built of Dhamma! "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ → sokāvakiṇṇaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.6"
msgid "Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ janatamapetasoko, "
msgstr "You’re free of sorrow; but look at these people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.7"
msgid "Avekkhassu jātijarābhibhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "overwhelmed with sorrow, oppressed by rebirth and old age. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc150
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.8"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi vīra vijitasaṅgāma, "
msgstr "Rise, hero! Victor in battle, leader of the caravan, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.9"
msgid "Satthavāha aṇaṇa vicara loke; "
msgstr "wander the world without obligation. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Desassu → desetu (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.10"
msgid "Desassu bhagavā dhammaṃ, "
msgstr "Let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.11"
msgid "Aññātāro bhavissantī’ti. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand!’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc151
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.12"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha Vipassī addressed that Great Brahmā in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc152
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.13"
msgid "‘Apārutā tesaṃ amatassa dvārā, "
msgstr "‘Flung open are the doors to the deathless! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.14"
msgid "Ye sotavanto pamuñcantu saddhaṃ; "
msgstr "Let those with ears to hear decide their faith. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.15"
msgid "Vihiṃsasaññī paguṇaṃ na bhāsiṃ, "
msgstr "Thinking it would be troublesome, Brahmā, I did not teach "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.16"
msgid "Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ manujesu brahme’ti. "
msgstr "the sophisticated, sublime Dhamma among humans.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.40, sc153
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.17"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā: ‘katāvakāso khomhi vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammadesanāyā’ti vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Then the Great Brahmā, knowing that his request for the Buddha Vipassī to teach the Dhamma had been granted, bowed and respectfully circled him, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.7.18"
msgid "13. Aggasāvakayuga "
msgstr "13. The Chief Disciples "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.8, sc154
msgctxt "dn14:3.8.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.8.2"
msgid "‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Who should I teach first of all? "

msgctxt "dn14:3.8.3"
msgid "ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti? "
msgstr "Who will quickly understand this teaching?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.8.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.8.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasanti paṇḍitā viyattā medhāvino dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātikā. "
msgstr "‘That Khaṇḍa, the king’s son, and Tissa, the high priest’s son, are astute, competent, clever, and have long had little dust in their eyes. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.8.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ khaṇḍassa ca rājaputtassa, tissassa ca purohitaputtassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, te imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissantī’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I teach them first of all? They will quickly understand this teaching.’ "

# NOTE: Comm takes khema as a proper name; it is a common name for sanctuaries in the Jatakas.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.9, sc155
msgctxt "dn14:3.9.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—bodhirukkhamūle antarahito bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā kheme migadāye pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the tree of awakening and reappeared near the capital city of Bandhumatī, in the deer park named Sanctuary. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: dāyapālaṃ → migadāyapālaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn14:3.9.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dāyapālaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha Vipassī addressed the park keeper, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.9.3"
msgid "‘ehi tvaṃ, samma dāyapāla, bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ pavisitvā khaṇḍañca rājaputtaṃ tissañca purohitaputtaṃ evaṃ vadehi—"
msgstr "‘My dear park keeper, please enter the city and say this to the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.9.4"
msgid "vipassī, bhante, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati, so tumhākaṃ dassanakāmo’ti. "
msgstr "“Sirs, the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, has arrived at Bandhumatī and is staying in the deer park named Sanctuary. He wishes to see you.”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.9.5"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bhante’ti kho, bhikkhave, dāyapālo vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa paṭissutvā bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ pavisitvā khaṇḍañca rājaputtaṃ tissañca purohitaputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "‘Yes, sir,’ replied the park keeper, and did as he was asked. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.9.6"
msgid "‘vipassī, bhante, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati; so tumhākaṃ dassanakāmo’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.10, pts-vp-pli2.41, sc156
msgctxt "dn14:3.10.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā niyyiṃsu. Yena khemo migadāyo tena pāyiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa had the finest carriages harnessed. Then they mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out from Bandhumatī for the Sanctuary. "

#. VAR: pattikāva → pattikā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.10.2"
msgid "Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikāva yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "They went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached the Buddha Vipassī on foot. They bowed and sat down to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.11, sc157
#. VAR: anupubbiṃ kathaṃ → anupubbīkathaṃ (s1-3, km) | ānupubbikathaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:3.11.1"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The Buddha Vipassī taught them step by step, with "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.2"
msgid "dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.3"
msgid "Yadā te bhagavā aññāsi kallacitte muducitte vinīvaraṇacitte udaggacitte pasannacitte, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr "And when he knew that their minds were ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.4"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ. "
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya; "
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.6"
msgid "evameva khaṇḍassa ca rājaputtassa tissassa ca purohitaputtassa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.11.7"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti. "
msgstr "‘Everything that has a beginning has an end.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.12, pts-vp-pli2.42, sc158
msgctxt "dn14:3.12.1"
msgid "Te diṭṭhadhammā pattadhammā viditadhammā pariyogāḷhadhammā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "They saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. They went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. They said to the Buddha Vipassī, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.12.2"
msgid "‘abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "‘Excellent, sir! Excellent! "

msgctxt "dn14:3.12.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: “cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī”ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.12.4"
msgid "Ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca. "
msgstr "We go for refuge to the Blessed One, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.12.5"
msgid "Labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyāma upasampadan’ti. "
msgstr "Sir, may we receive the going forth and ordination in the Buddha’s presence?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.13, sc159
msgctxt "dn14:3.13.1"
msgid "Alatthuṃ kho, bhikkhave, khaṇḍo ca rājaputto, tisso ca purohitaputto vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ alatthuṃ upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And they received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha Vipassī’s presence. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.13.2"
msgid "Te vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi; "
msgstr "Then the Buddha Vipassī educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them with a Dhamma talk. "

#. VAR: nibbāne → nibbāne va (bj) | nekkhamme (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn14:3.13.3"
msgid "saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ nibbāne ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "He explained the drawbacks of conditioned phenomena, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of extinguishment. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.13.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassiyamānānaṃ samādapiyamānānaṃ samuttejiyamānānaṃ sampahaṃsiyamānānaṃ nacirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu. "
msgstr "Being taught like this their minds were soon freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.13.5"
msgid "14. Mahājanakāyapabbajjā "
msgstr "14. The Going Forth of the Large Crowd "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.14, pts-vp-pli2.43, sc160
msgctxt "dn14:3.14.1"
msgid "Assosi kho, bhikkhave, bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni: "
msgstr "A large crowd of 84,000 people in the capital of Bandhumatī heard "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.2"
msgid "‘vipassī kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati. "
msgstr "that the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, had arrived at Bandhumatī and was staying in the deer park named Sanctuary. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.3"
msgid "Khaṇḍo ca kira rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā’ti. "
msgstr "And they heard that the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa had shaved off their hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and gone forth from the lay life to homelessness in the Buddha’s presence. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.4"
msgid "Sutvāna nesaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to them, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.5"
msgid "‘na hi nūna so orako dhammavinayo, na sā orakā pabbajjā, yattha khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā. "
msgstr "‘This must be no ordinary teaching and training, no ordinary going forth in which the king’s son Khaṇḍa and the high priest’s son Tissa have gone forth. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.6"
msgid "Khaṇḍo ca rājaputto tisso ca purohitaputto kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissanti, kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti. "
msgstr "If even they go forth, why don’t we do the same?’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.14.7"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahājanakāyo caturāsītipāṇasahassāni bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā nikkhamitvā yena khemo migadāyo yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then those 84,000 people left Bandhumatī for the deer park named Sanctuary, where they approached the Buddha Vipassī, bowed and sat down to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.15, sc161
msgctxt "dn14:3.15.1"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi. "
msgstr "The Buddha Vipassī taught them step by step, with "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.3"
msgid "Yadā te bhagavā aññāsi kallacitte muducitte vinīvaraṇacitte udaggacitte pasannacitte, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr "And when he knew that their minds were ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.4"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ. "
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya; "
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.6"
msgid "evameva tesaṃ caturāsītipāṇasahassānaṃ tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in those 84,000 people: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.7"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman’ti. "
msgstr "‘Everything that has a beginning has an end.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc162
msgctxt "dn14:3.15.8"
msgid "Te diṭṭhadhammā pattadhammā viditadhammā pariyogāḷhadhammā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṃkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "They saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. They went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. They said to the Buddha Vipassī, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.9"
msgid "‘abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "‘Excellent, sir! Excellent!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: “cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī”ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "And just like Khaṇḍa and Tissa they asked for and received ordination. Then the Buddha taught them further. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.11"
msgid "Ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.15.12"
msgid "Labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ labheyyāma upasampadan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.17, pts-vp-pli2.44, sc163
msgctxt "dn14:3.17.1"
msgid "Alatthuṃ kho, bhikkhave, tāni caturāsītipāṇasahassāni vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alatthuṃ upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.17.2"
msgid "Te vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.17.3"
msgid "saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ nibbāne ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.17.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ vipassinā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassiyamānānaṃ samādapiyamānānaṃ samuttejiyamānānaṃ sampahaṃsiyamānānaṃ nacirasseva anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu. "
msgstr "Being taught like this their minds were soon freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.17.5"
msgid "15. Purimapabbajitānaṃ dhammābhisamaya "
msgstr "15. The 84,000 Who Had Gone Forth Previously "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.18, sc164
msgctxt "dn14:3.18.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho, bhikkhave, tāni purimāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni: "
msgstr "The 84,000 people who had gone forth previously also heard: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.18.2"
msgid "‘vipassī kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ anuppatto kheme migadāye viharati, dhammañca kira desetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘It seems the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, has arrived at Bandhumatī and is staying in the deer park named Sanctuary. And he is teaching the Dhamma!’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.18.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, tāni caturāsītipabbajitasahassāni yena bandhumatī rājadhānī yena khemo migadāyo yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then they too went to see the Buddha Vipassī, realized the Dhamma, went forth, and became freed from defilements. "

