#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.21.5"
msgid "16. Cārikāanujānana "
msgstr "16. The Allowance to Wander "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.22, pts-vp-pli2.46, sc168
msgctxt "dn14:3.22.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā mahābhikkhusaṅgho paṭivasati aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time a large Saṅgha of 6,800,000 mendicants were residing at Bandhumatī. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "As the Buddha Vipassī was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.3"
msgid "‘mahā kho etarahi bhikkhusaṅgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, yannūnāhaṃ bhikkhū anujāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "‘The Saṅgha residing at Bandhumatī now is large. What if I was to urge them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.22.4"
msgid "“caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ; "
msgstr "“Wander forth, mendicants, for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.5"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha; "
msgstr "Let not two go by one road. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.6"
msgid "desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha. "
msgstr "Teach the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.7"
msgid "Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
msgstr "There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.8"
msgid "bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand the teaching! "

msgctxt "dn14:3.22.9"
msgid "Api ca channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā”’ti. "
msgstr "But when six years have passed, you must all come to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.23, pts-vp-pli2.47, sc169
msgctxt "dn14:3.23.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro mahābrahmā vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito vipassissa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then a certain Great Brahmā, knowing what the Buddha Vipassī was thinking, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha Vipassī. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.2"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mahābrahmā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha Vipassī, and said, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.3"
msgid "‘evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "‘That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.4"
msgid "Mahā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhusaṃgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ, anujānātu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhū: "
msgstr "The Saṅgha residing at Bandhumatī now is large. Please urge them to wander, as you thought. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.5"
msgid "“caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.6"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.7"
msgid "desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: aññātāro”ti → aññātāro (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn14:3.23.8"
msgid "Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.9"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, mayaṃ tathā karissāma yathā bhikkhū channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamissanti pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "And sir, I’ll make sure that when six years have passed the mendicants will return to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.23.10"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā. "
msgstr "That’s what that Great Brahmā said. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.23.11"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā vipassiṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha Vipassī, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.24, sc170
msgctxt "dn14:3.24.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha Vipassī came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants, telling them all that had happened. Then he said, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.24.2"
msgid "‘idha mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.24.3"
msgid "“mahā kho etarahi bhikkhusaṅgho bandhumatiyā rājadhāniyā paṭivasati aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.24.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ bhikkhū anujāneyyaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.24.5"
msgid "caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.24.6"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha; "
msgstr " "

