msgid "caratha, bhikkhave, cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.25.7"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.25.8"
msgid "desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.25.9"
msgid "santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāroti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.25.10"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, mayaṃ tathā karissāma, yathā bhikkhū channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamissanti pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.25.11"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so mahābrahmā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.25.12"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.26, sc172
msgctxt "dn14:3.26.1"
msgid "‘Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caratha cārikaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Wander forth, mendicants, for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.26.2"
msgid "mā ekena dve agamittha; "
msgstr "Let not two go by one road. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.26.3"
msgid "desetha, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetha. "
msgstr "Teach the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.26.4"
msgid "Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti, "
msgstr "There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.26.5"
msgid "bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand the teaching! "

msgctxt "dn14:3.26.6"
msgid "Api ca, bhikkhave, channaṃ channaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "But when six years have passed, you must all come to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.26.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yebhuyyena ekāheneva janapadacārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then most of the mendicants departed to wander the country that very day. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.27, pts-vp-pli2.49, sc173
msgctxt "dn14:3.27.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena jambudīpe caturāsīti āvāsasahassāni honti. "
msgstr "Now at that time there were 84,000 monasteries in India. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.2"
msgid "Ekamhi hi vasse nikkhante devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ: "
msgstr "And when the first year came to an end the deities raised the cry: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.3"
msgid "‘nikkhantaṃ kho, mārisā, ekaṃ vassaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Good sirs, the first year has ended. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.4"
msgid "pañca dāni vassāni sesāni; "
msgstr "Now five years remain. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.5"
msgid "pañcannaṃ vassānaṃ accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "When five years have passed, you must all go to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.27.6"
msgid "Dvīsu vassesu nikkhantesu … "
msgstr "And when the second year … "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.7"
msgid "tīsu vassesu nikkhantesu … "
msgstr "the third year … "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.8"
msgid "catūsu vassesu nikkhantesu … "
msgstr "the fourth year … "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.9"
msgid "pañcasu vassesu nikkhantesu devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ: "
msgstr "the fifth year came to an end, the deities raised the cry: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.10"
msgid "‘nikkhantāni kho, mārisā, pañcavassāni; "
msgstr "‘Good sirs, the fifth year has ended. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.11"
msgid "ekaṃ dāni vassaṃ sesaṃ; "
msgstr "Now one year remains. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.12"
msgid "ekassa vassassa accayena bandhumatī rājadhānī upasaṅkamitabbā pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "When one year has passed, you must all go to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.27.13"
msgid "Chasu vassesu nikkhantesu devatā saddamanussāvesuṃ: "
msgstr "And when the sixth year came to an end the deities raised the cry: "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.14"
msgid "‘nikkhantāni kho, mārisā, chabbassāni, "
msgstr "‘Good sirs, the sixth year has ended. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.15"
msgid "samayo dāni bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamituṃ pātimokkhuddesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "Now is the time that you must go to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code.’ "

msgctxt "dn14:3.27.16"
msgid "Atha kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū appekacce sakena iddhānubhāvena appekacce devatānaṃ iddhānubhāvena ekāheneva bandhumatiṃ rājadhāniṃ upasaṅkamiṃsu pātimokkhuddesāyāti. "
msgstr "Then that very day the mendicants went to Bandhumatī to recite the monastic code. Some went by their own psychic power, and some by the psychic power of the deities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.28, sc174
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.1"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhikkhusaṅghe evaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisati: "
msgstr "And there the Blessed One Vipassī, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, recited the monastic code thus: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc175
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.2"
msgid "‘Khantī paramaṃ tapo titikkhā, "
msgstr "‘Patient acceptance is the highest austerity. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.3"
msgid "Nibbānaṃ paramaṃ vadanti buddhā; "
msgstr "Extinguishment is the highest, say the Buddhas. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.4"
msgid "Na hi pabbajito parūpaghātī, "
msgstr "No true renunciate injures another, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.5"
msgid "Na samaṇo hoti paraṃ viheṭhayanto. "
msgstr "nor does an ascetic hurt another. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc176
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.6"
msgid "Sabbapāpassa akaraṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Not to do any evil; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.7"
msgid "kusalassa upasampadā; "
msgstr "to embrace the good; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.8"
msgid "Sacittapariyodapanaṃ, "
msgstr "to purify one’s mind: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.9"
msgid "etaṃ buddhānasāsanaṃ. "
msgstr "this is the instruction of the Buddhas. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.50, sc177
#. VAR: Anūpavādo anūpaghāto → anupavādo anupaghāto (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.10"
msgid "Anūpavādo anūpaghāto, "
msgstr "Not speaking ill nor doing harm; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.11"
msgid "Pātimokkhe ca saṃvaro; "
msgstr "restraint in the monastic code; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.12"
msgid "Mattaññutā ca bhattasmiṃ, "
msgstr "moderation in eating; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.13"
msgid "Pantañca sayanāsanaṃ; "
msgstr "staying in remote lodgings; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.14"
msgid "Adhicitte ca āyogo, "
msgstr "commitment to the higher mind—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.15"
msgid "Etaṃ buddhānasāsanan’ti. "
msgstr "this is the instruction of the Buddhas.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn14:3.28.16"
msgid "17. Devatārocana "
msgstr "17. Being Informed by Deities "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.29, pts-vp-pli2.51, sc178
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, bhikkhave, samayaṃ ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ viharāmi subhagavane sālarājamūle. "
msgstr "At one time, mendicants, I was staying near Ukkaṭṭhā, in the Subhaga Forest at the root of a magnificent <i>sal</i> tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.2"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "As I was in private retreat this thought came to mind, "

#. VAR: anāvutthapubbo → anaj­jhā­vuttha­pubbo (bj) | anaj­jhā­vuṭṭha­pubbo (mr)
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.3"
msgid "‘na kho so sattāvāso sulabharūpo, yo mayā anāvutthapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā aññatra suddhāvāsehi devehi. "
msgstr "‘It’s not easy to find an abode of sentient beings where I haven’t previously abided in all this long time, except for the gods of the pure abodes. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena suddhāvāsā devā tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go to see them?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ subhagavane sālarājamūle antarahito avihesu devesu pāturahosiṃ. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, I vanished from the Subhaga Forest and reappeared with the Aviha gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.6"
msgid "Tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "In that order of gods, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands of deities approached me, bowed, stood to one side, and said to me, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.7"
msgid "‘ito so, mārisā, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr "‘Ninety-one eons ago, good sir, the Buddha Vipassī arose in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.8"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi, khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr "He was born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.9"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr "Koṇḍañña was his clan. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.10"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "He lived for 80,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.11"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "He was awakened at the root of a trumpet flower tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.12"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "He had a fine pair of chief disciples named Khaṇḍa and Tissa. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.13"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ. Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni. Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "He had three gatherings of disciples—one of 6,800,000, one of 100,000, and one of 80,000—all of them mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.14"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "He had as chief attendant a mendicant named Asoka. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.15"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "His father was King Bandhuma, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.16"
msgid "Bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "his birth mother was Queen Bandhumatī, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.17"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and their capital city was named Bandhumatī. "

# NOTE: This is basically a table of contents for any Buddha biography.
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.18"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ ahosi evaṃ pabbajjā evaṃ padhānaṃ evaṃ abhisambodhi evaṃ dhammacakkappavattanaṃ. "
msgstr "And such was his renunciation, such his going forth, such his striving, such his awakening, and such his rolling forth of the wheel of Dhamma. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.29.19"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, mārisā, vipassimhi bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti … "
msgstr "And good sir, after leading the spiritual life under that Buddha Vipassī we lost our desire for sensual pleasures and were reborn here.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: While this is absent here, they are all mentioned below, and comm says they should be included here. This must be just a clumsy abbreviation.
msgctxt "dn14:3.29.20"
msgid "pe … "
msgstr "And other deities came and similarly recounted the details of the Buddhas Sikhī, Vessabhū, Kakusandha, Koṇāgamana, and Kassapa. "

# NOTE: In PTS, unlike MS, the deities who came to see the Buddha are numbered as “hundreds”, which seems more reasonable. RD has this, while MW does not.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.30, pts-vp-pli2.52, sc179
msgctxt "dn14:3.30.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃyeva kho, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "In that order of gods, many hundreds of deities approached me, bowed, stood to one side, and said to me, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.2"
msgid "‘imasmiṃyeva kho, mārisā, bhaddakappe bhagavā etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno. "
msgstr "‘In the present fortunate eon, good sir, you have arisen in the world, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.3"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, khattiyo jātiyā khattiyakule uppanno. "
msgstr "You were born as an aristocrat into an aristocrat family. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.4"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, gotamo gottena. "
msgstr "Gotama is your clan. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.5"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ yo ciraṃ jīvati, so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo. "
msgstr "For you the life-span is short, brief, and fleeting. A long-lived person lives for a century or a little more. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.6"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, assatthassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr "You were awakened at the root of a peepul tree. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.7"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "You have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.8"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni. Bhagavato, mārisā, ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr "You have had one gathering of disciples—1,250 mendicants who had ended their defilements. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.9"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, ānando nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "You have as chief attendant a mendicant named Ānanda. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.10"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, suddhodano nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr "Your father is King Suddhodana, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.11"
msgid "Māyā nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr "your birth mother was Queen Māyā, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.12"
msgid "Kapilavatthu nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr "and your capital city was Kapilavatthu. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.13"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ ahosi evaṃ pabbajjā evaṃ padhānaṃ evaṃ abhisambodhi evaṃ dhammacakkappavattanaṃ. "
msgstr "And such was your renunciation, such your going forth, such your striving, such your awakening, and such your rolling forth of the wheel of Dhamma. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.30.14"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, mārisā, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr "And good sir, after leading the spiritual life under you we lost our desire for sensual pleasures and were reborn here.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.31, sc180
msgctxt "dn14:3.31.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avihehi devehi saddhiṃ yena atappā devā tenupasaṅkamiṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Then together with the Aviha gods I went to see the Atappa gods … "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.2"
msgid "atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avihehi ca devehi atappehi ca devehi saddhiṃ yena sudassā devā tenupasaṅkamiṃ. "
msgstr "the Gods Fair to See … "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.53, sc181
msgctxt "dn14:3.31.3"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avihehi ca devehi atappehi ca devehi sudassehi ca devehi saddhiṃ yena sudassī devā tenupasaṅkamiṃ. Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, avihehi ca devehi atappehi ca devehi sudassehi ca devehi sudassīhi ca devehi saddhiṃ yena akaniṭṭhā devā tenupasaṅkamiṃ. Tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "and the Fair Seeing Gods. Then together with all these gods I went to see the Gods of Akaniṭṭha, where we had a similar conversation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn14:3.31.4"
msgid "‘ito so, mārisā, ekanavutikappe yaṃ vipassī bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke udapādi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.5"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho khattiyo jātiyā ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.6"
msgid "Khattiyakule udapādi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.7"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho koṇḍañño gottena ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.8"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asītivassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.9"
msgid "Vipassī, mārisā, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pāṭaliyā mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.10"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa khaṇḍatissaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.11"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.12"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aṭṭhasaṭṭhibhikkhusatasahassaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.13"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi bhikkhusatasahassaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.14"
msgid "Eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi asītibhikkhusahassāni. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.15"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ime tayo sāvakānaṃ sannipātā ahesuṃ sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.16"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa asoko nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.17"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bandhumā nāma rājā pitā ahosi bandhumatī nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.18"
msgid "Bandhumassa rañño bandhumatī nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.19"
msgid "Vipassissa, mārisā, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ ahosi evaṃ pabbajjā evaṃ padhānaṃ evaṃ abhisambodhi, evaṃ dhammacakkappavattanaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.20"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, mārisā, vipassimhi bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.21"
msgid "Tasmiṃyeva kho, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.22"
msgid "‘ito so, mārisā, ekatiṃse kappe yaṃ sikhī bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.23"
msgid "te mayaṃ, mārisā, sikhimhi bhagavati tasmiññeva kho, mārisā, ekatiṃse kappe yaṃ vessabhū bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.24"
msgid "te mayaṃ, mārisā, vessabhumhi bhagavati … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.25"
msgid "imasmiṃyeva kho, mārisā, bhaddakappe kakusandho koṇāgamano kassapo bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.31.26"
msgid "te mayaṃ, mārisā, kakusandhamhi koṇāgamanamhi kassapamhi bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.32, sc182
msgctxt "dn14:3.32.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃyeva kho, bhikkhave, devanikāye anekāni devatāsahassāni anekāni devatāsatasahassāni yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.2"
msgid "‘imasmiṃyeva kho, mārisā, bhaddakappe bhagavā etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.3"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, khattiyo jātiyā, khattiyakule uppanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.4"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, gotamo gottena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.5"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ yo ciraṃ jīvati, so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.6"
msgid "Bhagavā, mārisā, assatthassa mūle abhisambuddho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.7"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.8"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.9"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, ayaṃ eko sāvakānaṃ sannipāto ahosi sabbesaṃyeva khīṇāsavānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.10"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, ānando nāma bhikkhu upaṭṭhāko aggupaṭṭhāko ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.11"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, suddhodano nāma rājā pitā ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.12"
msgid "Māyā nāma devī mātā ahosi janetti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.13"
msgid "Kapilavatthu nāma nagaraṃ rājadhānī ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.14"
msgid "Bhagavato, mārisā, evaṃ abhinikkhamanaṃ ahosi, evaṃ pabbajjā, evaṃ padhānaṃ, evaṃ abhisambodhi, evaṃ dhammacakkappavattanaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn14:3.32.15"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, mārisā, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ caritvā kāmesu kāmacchandaṃ virājetvā idhūpapannā’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3.33, pts-vp-pli2.54, sc183
msgctxt "dn14:3.33.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgatassevesā dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā, yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati ‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ’ itipi. "
msgstr "And that is how the Realized One is able to recollect the caste, names, clans, life-span, chief disciples, and gatherings of disciples of the Buddhas of the past who have become completely extinguished, cut off proliferation, cut off the track, finished off the cycle, and transcended suffering. It is both because I have clearly comprehended the principle of the teachings, "

msgctxt "dn14:3.33.2"
msgid "‘Evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ’ itipīti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc184
msgctxt "dn14:3.33.3"
msgid "Devatāpi tathāgatassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ, yena tathāgato atīte buddhe parinibbute chinnapapañce chinnavaṭume pariyādinnavaṭṭe sabbadukkhavītivatte jātitopi anussarati, nāmatopi anussarati, gottatopi anussarati, āyuppamāṇatopi anussarati, sāvakayugatopi anussarati, sāvakasannipātatopi anussarati ‘evaṃjaccā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ’ itipi. "
msgstr "and also because the deities told me.” "

msgctxt "dn14:3.33.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃnāmā evaṅgottā evaṃsīlā evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ’ itipī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc185
msgctxt "dn14:3.33.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn14:3.33.6"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn14:3.33.7"
msgid "Mahāpadānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

